?</span><hr size=1> If you only had room for one which would you get? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=seductroo>seductroo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/5/03 10:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dex or Quick on SC armor?</span><hr size=1> In most cases i would say:<br>
<br>
Dex if you use a 2 hander<br>
Qui if you use a 1 hander<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Padar,<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--> <!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->50 Kobold Skald Palomides</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=leorik69>Leorik69</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/10/03 11:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dex or Quick on SC armor?</span><hr size=1> In all cases... Dex.<br>
 <p>Leorik Kinslayer~Hand of Bragi~ Flammen Herra - Nimue</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=torlynn>Torlynn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/11/03 2:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dex or Quick on SC armor?</span><hr size=1> That is so backwards.<br>
<br>
If you use a 2h, you want quick more. Quickness increases your attack speed by a percentage, thus if you are using a slower weapon that percentage will be greater and your damage will be increased by a like percentage..<br>
<br>
If you use a 1h, you want dex more. Quick won't impact a 1h as much because of faster attack speed, and higher dex will increase your block rate. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=leorik69>Leorik69</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/11/03 11:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dex or Quick on SC armor?</span><hr size=1> Dex &gt; Quick for 1h or 2h, it doesn't matter. Dex effects our chances to parry... Which is the only form of defense skalds have. It does NOTHING for our ability to block, as we can't spec in shield. The only way for dex to become a factor in blocking for skalds is if you have MoB 1 or higher...<br>
<br>
But don't get me wrong, I think quickness is important to, as it makes us swing faster and increases our evade rate slightly. But I'd rather have more solid defense than swinging slightly faster. So once you've maxed str/con/cha/skills/hits/resists I'd cap dex and throw whatever's left into quick. Easier said than done tho... <p>Leorik Kinslayer~Hand of Bragi~ Flammen Herra - Nimue</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=torlynn>Torlynn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/12/03 7:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dex or Quick on SC armor?</span><hr size=1> Eh, I was mostly replying to seductroo, as his advice was incorrect, it'd be the other way around, as quick is more important for a 2h user than a 1h user, and dex will have more of an impact on a 1h user, because if you're wielding a 1h you obviously have a shield in the other hand. It should also be noted that dex will increase your base chance to block, whether or not you have shield spec and/or MoB.<br>
<br>
Don't underestimate quickness. If you're using a slow enough weapon, a point of quick can do more for your damage than a point of str, and add to your chance to evade as well. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ororo7>Ororo7</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 75<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/16/03 4:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dex or Quick on SC armor?</span><hr size=1> Quick only helps in long fights right?  Because in short fights, harder hits up front will help more.<br>
<br>
Add in the ability to break up a fight with mez and snare, effectively restarting the battle timer, and again you might want low quick.<br>
<br>
Add in the fact that any <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8o --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/nerd.gif ALT="8o"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> n8 fights where a skald is assisting the main tanks, if you win enemies drop fast and if you lose you are probably stunned/mez.  Once again big hits and low quick might be preferred.<br>
<br>
So when do you want quick?  Maybe for 1on1 fights?  Certainly in small fights against pbt.  Fight clubs?  irc battles?<br>
<br>
Seems the case can be made either way, but Dex is always a plus.<br>
<br>
-Leitari, mlf <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gisborne>gisborne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 343<br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/19/03 4:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dex or Quick on SC armor?</span><hr size=1> 15% haste or 3% parry? Seems obvious to me.<br>
